This project's pipeline architecture (three phases / nine stages, multi-agent
voting for false-positive reduction, structured triage artifacts) is inspired
by publicly described designs from agentic-SAST research, including:

  - Anthropic's "Project Glasswing" public materials on AI-assisted
    vulnerability research.

  - Visa's open-source "Visa Vulnerability Agentic Harness" (VVAH),
    https://github.com/visa/visa-vulnerability-agentic-harness -- Apache-2.0.
    Influence: pipeline phases, multi-agent voting, skill-based extension,
    AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md operating files, SARIF emission patterns.

  - Rivian's open-source "ai-sast",
    https://github.com/rivian/ai-sast -- Apache-2.0.
    Influence: GitHub Actions integration, PR-scan / full-scan duality,
    PR-comment writer with TP/FP feedback checkboxes, feedback-loop
    storage (SQLite/Databricks), CVSS vectors, DoS limits, multi-cloud
    LLM backends (Bedrock, Vertex AI, Ollama), webhook notifications.

No code from VVAH or ai-sast is bundled in this repository; influence is
architectural only and is implemented from scratch here.

